cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.SY

This paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques (e.g., deep learning) for achieving cognitive self-organization in future communications and data networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of these techniques to adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges faced by CSON in meeting the requirements of next-generation networks, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
